back\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yga1665702577055.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yga1665702577055.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yga1665702577055.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yga1665702577055\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">$applname \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"yga1665702577055___applname_252454\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the name of the Application Shell.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"yga1665702577055__topic_d80369e1_d80370e1_d80371e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yga1665702577055__p_d80372e1_d80373e1_d80374e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applname</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yga1665702577055__topic_d52882e1_d52883e1_d52884e1_d52885e1_d52886e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d414612e66\">Return Values</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yga1665702577055__li_d33677e1_d33678e1_d33679e1\">String that contains the name of the current application shell (in uppercase).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yga1665702577055__li_d33680e1_d33681e1_d33682e1\">Name of its application server, if component is\n               remote (that is, a service, session service, entity service or report running on a\n               server) .</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yga1665702577055__topic_d52887e1_d52888e1_d52889e1_d52890e1_d52891e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d414612e81\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yga1665702577055__d6512e20\">Use only in Application Shell and Form components.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yga1665702577055__topic_d52892e1_d52893e1_d52894e1_d52895e1_d52896e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d414612e90\">Description</h2>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"yga1665702577055__note_w2957ab1b7b9b3_w2958ab1b7b9_w2959ab1b7_w2960ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The name is returned with uppercase letters, so this name is not necessarily the same as the application name seen by the operating system.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yga1665702577055__p_d80387e1_d80388e1_d80389e1\">For example, applications built on a Unix platform are created in lowercase, but <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applname</span> returns the Uniface application name, which is in uppercase.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yga1665702577055__p_d80390e1_d80391e1_d80392e1\">One use for <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applname</span> could be to restrict the use of a global ProcScript to certain (named) applications; a test on the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applname</span> at the start of the ProcScript module could prevent use of the module by returning immediately. If you distribute only the object code for your global ProcScript (in UAR files containing <span class=\"ph filepath\">/prc/*.prc</span> , for example) and not the source, you can use this technique to prevent unauthorized use of the global ProcScript.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yga1665702577055__section_mkw_lzq_zbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d414612e118\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applname</span></h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example outputs an initial message and a final message\n               when the Application Shell BOOK is run:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"yga1665702577055__pre_hzv_qzq_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; trigger: apStart\nputmess \"Started application %%$applname at %%$clock\"\nrun \"MAIN_MENU\"\nputmess \"Terminated application %%$applname at %%$clock\"\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jnc1665702576977.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$entname</a><p>Return the name of the current entity or check for the existence of an entity in the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jfn1665702577202.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldname</a><p>Return the name of the current field or check for the presence of a specified field in the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ksm1665702577277.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$instancename</a><p>Return the name of the current component instance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534076\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534076\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$applname Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $applname Return the name of the Application Shell. $applname Return Values String that contains the name of the current application shell (in uppercase). Name of its application server, if component is remote (that is, a service, session service, entity service or report running on a server) . Use Use only in Application Shell and Form components. Description Note: The name is returned with uppercase letters, so this name is not necessarily the same as the application name seen by the operating system. For example, applications built on a Unix platform are created in lowercase, but $applname returns the Uniface application name, which is in uppercase. One use for $applname could be to restrict the use of a global ProcScript to certain (named) applications; a test on the value of $applname at the start of the ProcScript module could prevent use of the module by returning immediately. If you distribute only the object code for your global ProcScript (in UAR files containing /prc/*.prc , for example) and not the source, you can use this technique to prevent unauthorized use of the global ProcScript. Example: Using $applname The following example outputs an initial message and a final message when the Application Shell BOOK is run: ; trigger: apStart putmess \"Started application %%$applname at %%$clock\" run \"MAIN_MENU\" putmess \"Terminated application %%$applname at %%$clock\" Copy Related Links $entname Return the name of the current entity or check for the existence of an entity in the component. $fieldname Return the name of the current field or check for the presence of a specified field in the component. $instancename Return the name of the current component instance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}